
1. Continuous Monitoring:
====================================
Continuous Monitoring it is a practice in Devops that  involves
 - collection of Metrics that we have to monitor 
 - Analysis of the metrics
 - Visualization of the metrics and data 
 - real time monitoring of clusters, containers, tools, applications, network
 - proactively detecting the issues.
 - helps is timely correcting and optimizing the system and application

Continuous Monitoring it is a practice done 
 - using monitoring tools 
    - using these tools we collect metrics , Analysis and visualize them 

Continuous Monitoring it is a practice that will
  - monitor Servers/VM
  - monitor your pipelines/workflows
  - monitor services on cloud 
  - monitor clusters
  - network devices
  - applications/databases

The main goal is to gain insights of the 
 - System/application behaviour, 
 - identify bottelnecks
 - take necessary actions 
 - so as to get reliable system 


Components of Continuous Monitoring:
1. Data collection: monitoring agents -> scraping metrics
  example:  application - logs 
            cluster - metrics(cpu, memory, network)  
Example: logstash, fluent beats, Prometheus

2. Data Analysis: 
      The collected data is analyzed to identify patterns, trends, conditions and anomalies
      and find performance issues, security threats and failures.
Example: Elastic Search, Prometheus

3. Visualization dashboards:
           Tools provides us dashboards where we can see all the metrics and data 
Example: Kibana, GRAFANA(integrates with Prometheus or cloudwatch or data dog, mysql to get the metrics/data)
      
4. Alerting and Notification:
     Monitoring tools connect with alert and notification tools like : slack, teams, email


EXAMPLE: NAGIOS, ELK


Demo 1: 

Install Prometheus on a VM 
Install Jenkins --> monitoring it using Prometheus
Install Grafana on the same VM --> pass jenkins data from Prometheus to Grafana 
Monitor the data on Grafana 

